Course provides further coverage of the grammatical and lexical systems of Latvian, combined with further practice of the listening, speaking, writing and reading skills. During the course, students will make interactive exercises, practice gap-fill exercises, and understanding the content of the text.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main aim of course is to enhance the learner's abilities in the use of Latvian and develop all four language skills (reading, writing, listening, speaking) through a variety of tasks. The course is designed for those who have finished the Latvian language courses for entry-level (at least in level A1.2), or for the people with equivalent knowledge of Latvian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student will have developed his readiness to communicate in Latvian, his/her oral and written expression and comprehension skills will have improved towards more clarity and fluency, due to his/her enriched vocabulary and better pronunciation.
